<H3> <TI>   Labor Minister Announces New Job Safety Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2501133994 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2501133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Labor Minister Luis Horacio Vivas Pena announced 
the opening of the National Occupational Welfare, Health, and 
Safety Institute [Instituto Nacional de Prevision, Salud, y 
Seguridad Laboral] at Miraflores Palace today. This 
organization is entrusted with the responsibility of watching 
over the workers' physical and mental environments. 
  [Begin Vivas recording] To further this objective, the law 
includes the establishment of two large organizations. One is 
the National Council and the other is the National Occupational 
Welfare, Health, and Safety Institute. The latter is the one 
that was established today. We inaugurated all its members, and 
they will begin advising the Executive Branch and union and 
business organizations on how to handle safety problems in the 
work place. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

