<H3> <TI>   URNG Says Referendum Seeks Legitimacy for Bad Conduct </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2601181994 Guatemala City EL GRAFICO in Spanish 25 Jan 94 
p 47 </F>

<F P=103> PA2601181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City EL GRAFICO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Paid advertisement from the Guatemalan National </F>
Revolutionary Unity, URNG; place and date not given] 
  [Text] URNG [Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity] 
  TO REJECT THE REFERENDUM IS TO ANNUL THE SCHEME 
  Appeal from the URNG: 
  Given the crisis in Guatemala, as evidenced by former 
President Jorge Serrano Elias' coup, the roles of the 
Legislative, Executive, and Judicial Branches have been totally 
discredited. 
  Guatemalan society rejects corruption, deceit, schemes, and 
fraud, and it refuses to continue to live with the impunity with 
which those state organizations act. 
  The 30 January referendum plans to legitimize the despicable 
political and moral conduct that has prevailed in the state 
branches for years. 
  The announced constitutional reforms are not the ones 
Guatemala needs and demands; they are schemes hatched behind 
civilian society's back that deliberately intend to worsen the 
national crisis. 
  The causes that led to the May 1993 coup d'etat remain 
unsolved. In-depth reforms, based on a different project for the 
construction of a new nation, are necessary to solve the 
institutional crisis. 

</TEXT>

