<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protocol Signed With PRC To Promote Pharmaceutical Exchange </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2701012194 Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 26 Jan 
94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY2701012194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Health Ministry and the PRC Pharmaceutical State 
Administration yesterday signed a protocol of intention with a 
view to promoting technical exchange in the pharmaceutical area. 
The Brazil news agency has reported that the document provides 
for, among other things, exchange of information in the areas of 
of raw material purchasing, final products, and the provision of 
technology. 
  Health Minister Henrique Santillo said that the government 
has great expectations over the expansion of bilateral 
cooperation with the PRC. The protocol provides for training 
and consultation services by professionals of the two countries, 
and for the possibility of creating joint medical and 
pharmaceutical facilities in Brazil and in the PRC. 
  The PRC mission, which is headed by PRC Pharmaceutical State 
Administration Director Huang Jive -- who signed the protocol on 
behalf of his country -- will stay in Brazil until tomorrow. A 
Brazilian mission made up of state laboratory directors and 
technicians from the National Health Control Secretariat will 
visit the PRC in April to observe the facilities of the PRC 
state company and to discuss the strengthening of the protocol 
terms. 

</TEXT>

