<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lage Calls for Eradication of Black Market Profiteers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2601142294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2601142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Politburo member Carlos Lage has called for the 
eradication of profiteers who are illegally filling their 
pockets in the black market. In a meeting with 102 presidents of 
the Havana People's Councils, Lage, also the secretary of the 
Council of Ministers, suggested that no more licenses be granted 
or that they be suspended for craftsmen whose products are made 
with raw materials of a dubious origin. 
  The participants in the meeting advocated the need to 
increase taxes on surplus profits and price regulations. 
Likewise, the presidents of the Havana People's Councils, 
stressed that domestic messengers ought to pay taxes since they 
are earning much more than what Interior Commerce established. 
Other issues discussed in the meeting were Havana's garbage 
removal system and the delivery of the winter campaign products 
to the people. 
  Pedro Chavez, president of the people's government in Havana 
and member of the Central Committee, was also present at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

