<H3> <TI>   Canadian-Made Transmitter Installed in Villa Clara </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2601172994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1253 
GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2601172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The installation of a modern 10-kilowatt radio 
transmitter for the Villa Clara CMHW provincial network will be 
concluded shortly. This new transmitter will allow optimum 
signal quality on 840 khz and it will cover a transmitting range 
which is almost three times the current range. In other words, 
it is three times superior to the current equipment. This is 
the first 10-kilowatt Canadian-made transmitter installed in the 
country. The work was begun last week by a group of 
Communications Ministry engineers and technicians. 
  In addition to the Villa Clara CMHW transmitter, a similar 
one is being installed for Radio Rebelde on 1180 khz. This will 
improve the signal of this national radio station in our 
territory [no specific location given]. 

</TEXT>

