  [Text] In his first State of the Union address, United 
States President Bill Clinton, has repeated his call for reform 
of both his nation's health care and welfare. He said he would 
veto any bill that does not contain universal health coverage. 
He also called for action to reduce crime and urged a ban on 
assault rifles. Public opinion polls s how that a majority of 
Americans liked the president's speech. The oposition leader in 
the Senate, Bob Dole, used charts to suggest that Mr. Clinton's 
healthcare reform plan means more governmental control. 

