<F P=102>  PA2601170194 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 26 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2601170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] National Defense Secretariat Communique No. 26 
states that as of today, the Office of Complaints and Attention 
to the Citizenry [Oficina de Quejas y Atencion a la Ciudadania], 
which is under the Office of the Inspector and Comptroller 
General of the Army and Air Force, has been established in San 
Cristobal de Las Casas. The office will have representatives 
in Tuxtla Gutierrez, Oxchuc, Ocosingo, Altamirano, Las 
Margaritas, and Comitan, among other cities. 
  The communique says the measure is being taken in order to 
see that the actions of military personnel toward the civilian 
population are aboveboard and as another guarantee of our strict 
respect for the civil rights of the aforementioned population. 

