<H3> <TI>   Molirena Reelects Ramirez as Party President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2601165494 Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA in Spanish 25 Jan 
94 p 8c </F>

<F P=103> PA2601165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alfredo Ramirez was reelected president of the 
Nationalist Liberal Republican Movement (Molirena) during the 
party's 23 January convention at the Atlapa Convention Center. 
Ramirez has served in various ministries and was once a 
presidential hopeful. He is currently a member of the Canal 
Commission Board of Directors. Alfredo Ramirez has headed 
Molirena for the past 10 years and has been unanimously 
reelected to another five-year term. 

</TEXT>

