<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   FARC Front Denies Participation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2701233694 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2701233694 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A FARC [Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia] 
front blamed for killing 35 people in Apartado over the weekend 
has denied its participation in the massacre by claiming the 
culprits are the same people responsible for the killings at 
Honduras, La Negra, and Pueblo Bello haciendas. 
  Today, the Hope, Peace, and Liberty Movement said it will 
not 
withdraw from the Uraba political pact. The movement's topmost 
leader, Senator Anibal Palacios, however, has said that FARC's 
Bolivarian Militias are the ones that massacred 35 people in La 
Chinita, Apartado, neighborhood. This is Palacios' reaction to a 
letter FARC addressed to Antioquia Governor Juan Gomez Martinez 
denying FARC participation in the massacre. 
  [Begin Gomez Martinez recording] We did not say that 
Patriotic Unity is responsible, but rather that the Guerrilla 
Coordinating Board and the Bolivarian Militias had a hand in the 
La Chinita massacre. [end recording] 
  This afternoon, the movement leaders met with Government 
Minister Fabio Villegas Ramirez, whom they have asked to be an 
international observer for Uraba. 
  [Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish on 26 January 
publishes a 400-word article on page 6-A reporting: "The Hope, 
Peace, and Liberty Movement's decision to withdraw from the 
follow-up table [mesa de seguimiento], which guarantees the 
existence of the political pact signed in Uraba on 23 November, 
produced an avalanche of reactions." The article also reports: 
"Government Minister Fabio Villegas said the commitment has not 
been broken" and he adds that the Hope, Peace, and Liberty 
Movement still recognizes the validity of the political pact 
that was signed."] 

</TEXT>

