<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A street demonstration is planned to support the 
resolutions of the popular congress. A rally is planned for 
today in Port-au-Prince to prompt the Haitian legislators to 
adopt the resolutions of the congress held in the National 
Theater from 18 to 20 January. The congress had asked for the 
formation of a consensus government to solve the crisis. Let us 
listen to a spokesman for the popular congress: 
  [Begin unidentified spokesman recording, in Creole] We are 
asking all citizens who are aware, as we are, of the seriousness 
of the situation to express solidarity with the Government of 
Public Security as an attempt to solve the crisis that we have 
been facing for too long. It is to undermine the bases of [word 
indistinct]. [end recording] 
  That was the assistant secretary general of the popular 
congress held on 18, 19 and 20 January by the Group of the Great 
North. 
  Another demonstration is due to be held this morning in 
Port-au-Prince in front of the parliament building to demand the 
lifting of the international sanctions and the embargo. 

