<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   AD To Expel Members For Supporting Other Parties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2701134594 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2701134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Marcano from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In accordance with a Democratic Action [AD] National 
Executive Committee decision made during a Monday morning 
meeting, more than 2,000 members will be expelled from the party. 
  The expulsion will include members who supported other 
political organizations during the recent campaign and those who 
were candidates of political parties with which AD had no 
alliances. The National Executive Committee also appointed a 
commission to conduct a political analysis of the departments to 
prepare for the national convention. 
  As for the new government, AD Organization Secretary Lewis 
Perez reiterated that his party will support all things deemed 
positive for the country, even though National Convergence and 
Movement Toward Socialism voted against AD leader Carmelo Lauria 
in the Chamber of Deputies. 
  [Begin Perez recording] The AD will support any action or 
decision made by President Rafael Caldera that will benefit the 
country. We are going to remain critical of and follow closely 
the implementation of the government program proposed by Caldera 
during the recent campaign. [end recording] 
  It was also revealed that the National Executive Committee 
will hold a special meeting this week for members to review the 
country's fiscal and economic situation and establish a solid 
position on the measures to be implemented by Dr. Rafael Caldera. 

</TEXT>

