<F P=103> PA2801120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cecilia Pachano from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] At the Miraflores Palace, Venezuelan Petroleum 
[Petroven] President Gustavo Roosen has said he is fairly 
optimistic about the achievements of the negotiations between 
Venezuela and the United States on measures restricting national 
fuels. 
  [Begin recording] [Pachano] Gustavo Roosen also said 
President-elect Rafael Caldera's team of advisers has advised 
him of Petroven's budget for next year and its guidelines. 
Roosen pointed out that he fully approves of the plans our main 
oil company will execute. 
  [Roosen] In fact, Caldera's adviser Julio Cesar Rodriguez 
attended the 30 December meeting, and we have met several times 
since that meeting. He fully approves of the budget guidelines. 
He also told me he approves of the 10-year plan, which 
encompasses all the objectives to significantly increase the 
supply of oil products. 
  In fact, as a multifaceted company, about 75 percent of our 
total sales, including cyclical sales, consist of oil products, 
and only 25 percent consist of crude oil sales. Since 1982, 
Petroven has been replacing crude oil exports for oil product 
exports in international markets. [end recording] 

