<H3> <TI>   Ross Stresses Importance of CTC Anniversary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2701135694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2701135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pedro Ross Leal, member of the Politburo and 
secretary general of the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC], has 
stressed that the 55th anniversary of the CTC is a patriotic 
celebration which ought to contribute to consummate the workers' 
commitment to defend the Revolution and the accomplishments of 
socialism. Ross added that the unity of the labor movement 
anticipated by the founders of the CTC during the period of the 
pseudo-republic, inspires today's workers to confront the 
criminal U.S. blockade. Likewise, Ross pointed out that in this 
new anniversary of the CTC, Cuban workers are seeking new ways 
to attain higher economic efficiency and alternatives to 
streamline the national finances. 
  Pedro Ross also announced that the 55th CTC Anniversary pin 
will be given, for the first time, to 66 founder members and 
union leaders on 28 January in recognition of their work in the 
labor movement. 

</TEXT>

