<H3> <TI>   UN Ambassador Elected to Palestinian Rights Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2801025094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2801025094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A PRENSA LATINA news report says Ambassador Fernando 
Remirez Estenoz, Cuba's permanent representative to the United 
Nations, was today elected vice chairman of the special 
committee for the restoration of the legitimate rights of the 
Palestinian people. The Cuban diplomat, chosen by acclamation, 
was proposed by the Tunisian delegation and supported by Mali. 
  Upon addressing this UN committee, Remirez Estenoz 
highlighted the efforts to be made at a moment when the 
committee is entering a qualitatively different phase of its 
work following endorsement of the declaration of principles 
between Israel and Palestine. Remirez highlighted the duties to 
be assumed in order to contribute to monitoring the agreed-upon 
measures and to determine what assistance the United Nations 
must provide so the process can continue until restitution of 
the legitimate rights of the Palestinian people -- including 
that of the creation of their own state -- has been achieved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

