<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   URNG Reportedly Downs Power Tower </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2801152994 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 1400 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2801152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Guatemala Flash" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Alleged URNG [Guatemalan National Revolutionary 
Unity] cells downed and destroyed three power transmission 
towers last night. This happened in Las Ilusiones, Zone 18, 
Villa del Dorado, Zone 8, and the Ulises Rojas neighborhood at 
the 21-km marker on the Pacific highway, Villa Nueva 
Jurisdiction. Powerful charges downed the towers, causing a 
blackout in Guatemala City and the interior of the country. The 
blast hit Lirio Bolanos Rosas, a National Police employee of the 
National Police, on Zone 18, and had to be hospitalized. Last 
night and early this morning, technicians of the electricity 
company and INDE [National Institute of Electrification] 
estimated the damage caused at 500,000 quetzales. They did not 
make estimates on the serious damage the blackout caused to 
homes, hospitals, clinics, and computer centers, as well as to 
citizens who were the victims of crimes perpetrated under cover 
of the hour-long blackout in Guatemala City. The bomb squad 
defused a powerful device in the Ulises Rojas Neighborhood. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

