<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explosion Downs Third Power Pylon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2801125094 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 0542 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2801125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 27 Jan (ACAN-EFE) -- Firemen have 
reported that unidentified persons have downed a power pylon, 
the third to experience this fate in the past two hours, thus 
creating a blackout in Guatemala, the second today in this 
country. 
  According to municipal firemen, an earlier explosion of a 
dynamite charge injured three persons and destroyed a tower 
northeast of this capital, which has a population of more than 1 
million. 
  Another tower in the town of San Cristobal, south of the 
capital, was damaged by a bomb that exploded at approximately 
2130 (0330 GMT). 
  The firemen have said that there is no confirmation of 
whether the first reported explosion was produced by a dynamite 
attack. 
  The downing of the power pylons produced blackouts in the 
capital and in Solola and Chimaltenango Departments in the west 
and in Jutiapa and Santa Rosa Departments in the southeast of 
this Central American country, the only country in the area 
where guerrilla violence continues. 
  The attacks are taking place on the eve of a strike by 
200,000 state employees; in the absence of Guatemalan President 
Ramiro De Leon Carpio, who is staying overnight in Honduras; and 
only 48 hours prior to a referendum to reform the Constitution 
to advance the legislative elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

