<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unidentified Individuals Fire At U.S. Embassy; No Injuries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2801122094 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 0612 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2801122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 28 Jan (ACAN-EFE) -- A group of 
unidentified individuals fired at the U.S. Embassy in Guatemala 
City on Thursday shortly before midnight while almost the entire 
city was without electricity because three high tension towers 
were blown up, the Guatemalan police reported today. 
  A spokesman for the security forces told ACAN-EFE that 
unidentified persons inside a vehicle fired at the diplomatic 
mission as they drove by. No one was injured, and there was no 
property damage. 
  Embassy guards did not repel the attack, which took place at 
around 2330 (0530 GMT Friday), when the city was still without 
power as a result of three downed high tension towers in 
different areas of the outskirts of the city. No organization 
has claimed responsibility for the attack. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-51993 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat019_g_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-019 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  29 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Shots Fired </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2801124194 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0645 GMT 28 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2801124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 28 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- Unidentified men 
in a moving vehicle last night fired into the air in front of 
the U.S. Embassy, where approximately 600 peasants are 
demonstrating to demand the U.S. mission's intervention in the 
solution of a land conflict. 
  Eyewitnesses and security guards at the U.S. Embassy 
confirmed that at 2345 (0545 GMT), several individuals in a blue 
car fired several shots. 
  The peasants, who are members of the Federation of Workers 
and Laborers [Federacion de Trabajadores y Obreros], early this 
morning are patrolling the area with sticks and machetes to ward 
off attacks. The Indians have been in front of the embassy for 
three days to request the mission's mediation with the "Penny 
Foundation" [Fundacion del Centavo], which charges them 
excessive interest rates on loans made to families to buy land 
and build houses. 
  The attack is part of the wave of violence prevailing in the 
Guatemalan capital, where in the last four hours unidentified 
individuals set off explosive charges at electricity pylons. 
There is unease among the Guatemalan people 48 hours before a 
referendum is held to reform the Legislative and Judicial 
Branches and shorten the presidential term from five to four 
years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

