<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 27 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2701150994 </F>
<F P=103> PY2701150994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities monitored through 27 January. 
Source is listed in parentheses following each item: 
  Finance Minister Fernando Illanes signed a loan agreement 
for 
32 million German marks -- $18.6 million -- with the German 
Government. The funds will be used to supply electricity to 
Larecaja Province and La Paz Department and potable water to 
Oruro Department. (La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 31 Dec 93 p B2) 
  Fedor Perez, deputy director general of the General Customs 
Directorate, DGA, reported that the DGA collected 946 million 
bolivianos in 1993, a 17.9 percent increase compared with 1993. 
But he said this was less than national budget estimates due to 
international agreements signed with Colombia, Ecuador, 
Venezuela, Peru, Argentina, and Chile that provide for the 
reduction or exemption of tariffs. (La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 
11 Jan 94 p B5) 

