<F P=101> Jamaica </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Announces Supplemental Budget Plans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2701171994 Bridgetown CANA in English 1516 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> FL2701171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bridgetown CANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kingston, Jamaica, 27 Jan, CANA -- The Jamaica 
Government has tabled supplementary estimates in parliament 
seeking an additional three billion dollars to finance its 
1993/94 budget. 
  The revised estimates which are likely to be approved early 
next month will increase the budget for the financial year to 
43.392 billion dollars (one Jamaican dollar just over three US 
cents) from the original 40.371 billion dollars. 
  The additional money will go to recurrent or housekeeping 
expenses, which move up from 28.146 billion dollars to 31.758 
billion dollars while the capital side of the budget has been 
slashed by 591 million dollars from 12.225 billion dollars to 
11.634 billion dollars. 
  The greater portion of the increase will cover public debt 
payments and public sector salaries. 

</TEXT>

