<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   PMDB, PSDB To Sponsor Separate Presidential Candidates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2701234394 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2200 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2701234394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The PMDB [Brazilian Democratic Movement Party] and 
the PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy Party] will vote together 
on the constitutional reform, but will sponsor separate 
presidential candidates. 
  In Brasilia today, the executive boards of the two parties 
held separate meetings. 
  The PMDB will adopt a single position for the vote on the 
constitutional reform. The decision was made by the party 
executive board. Party positions will be studied on a weekly 
basis. 
  As for the presidential succession, the majority believes 
there should be an internal survey to choose a candidate. The 
new party program will be submitted to the national party 
convention in March. 
  Deputy Luiz Henrique, the PMDB president, will lead the 
drive 
for unity within the party and for future alliances. He began 
by talking with members of the PSDB, whose executive board also 
met in Brasilia today. 
  The two parties consider it possible to form an alliance as 
early as in the first electoral round, will continue to 
negotiate, but will not give up the designation of their own 
candidates for president. 
  [Begin PSDB President Tasso Jereissati recording] During a 
national party congress, the PSDB decided to run its own 
presidential candidate. [end recording] 
  [Begin PMDB President Luiz Henrique recording] Initially, 
the 
PMDB will strive to sponsor its own candidate. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

