<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner Urges More Respect for Church </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2701182894 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2701182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Manuel Camacho Solis, Chiapas State peace and 
reconciliation commissioner, has called for more respect for the 
role of churches in the conflict area so as not to provoke forms 
of violence. After meeting with evangelicals on 26 January, 
Camacho considered as very damaging to the peace process the 
statements accusing church members of instigating the armed 
conflict. He explained this could create new forms of violence 
instead of contributing to the resolution of the situation. 
  After leaving Los Pinos Residence, where he met with 
President Salinas de Gortari, Camacho announced that things are 
moving on the right track, adding that at noon on 27 January he 
will report the results of the measures taken to the Zapatist 
National Liberation Army forces. 

</TEXT>

