<H3> <TI>   Postpones Reply to EZLN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2701200794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1907 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2701200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Mexico City, 27 Jan (EFE) -- Manuel Camacho 
Solis, presidential commissioner for peace and reconciliation, 
today unexpectedly postponed his reply to the demands of the 
Zapatist National Liberation Army (EZLN) for a possible dialogue 
to end the armed conflict in Chiapas State. 
  Camacho said the postponement of the reply, which had been 
announced on 25 January for 1800 GMT today, is due to the fact 
that he had received in the last few hours "new information and 
elements that allow progress toward a dialogue." 
  Camacho reiterated that the only objective of this entire 
effort is achieving an end to hostilities, and that is why he 
decided to postpone the reply. "This is a delicate moment, which 
we must handle with utmost responsibility," Camacho Solis said. 
[passage omitted] 
  Camacho's announcement has created a great deal of 
anticipation in Mexico City, where there is conjecture about the 
origin of the new information received by the presidential peace 
commissioner. The peace commissioner and Bishop Samuel Ruiz of 
San Cristobal de las Casas (Chiapas) are in the Mexican capital. 
The bishop has been appointed the Mexican Government's mediator 
with the EZLN rebels. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

