<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 27 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2701152894 </F>
<F P=103> PY2701152894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Paraguay monitored through 27 
January. Source is listed in parentheses following each item: 
  A General Customs Directorate report notes that export 
earnings in 1993 were $748,145,804.64 -- free-on-board value, a 
15.3 percent rise compared with the previous year. Exports rose 
33.5 percent, totaling 2,783,377.6 metric tons. Paraguay's 
chief exports were soybeans, uncarded cotton, wood, leather, 
furs, and frozen beef. Its main trading partners were Brazil, 
which accounted for 30.1 percent of Paraguayan export earnings, 
followed by the Netherlands, 25.4 percent; Argentina, 9 percent; 
the United States, 8.7 percent; Chile, 6.1 percent; and 
Switzerland, 3.7 percent. (Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 25 Jan 
94 p 13) 
  The Inter-American Development Bank and the 
Argentine-Paraguayan Yacyreta Company on 27 January signed a 
$130 million loan agreement in Washington. This agreement 
includes the implementation of projects to alleviate the 
environmental impact of the hydroelectric dam's construction and 
several infrastructure and housing development programs to 
resettle 10,000 families, industries, and shops. (Asuncion ABC 
COLOR in Spanish 27 Jan 94 p 30) 

</TEXT>

