<H3> <TI>   PT President Lula Meets Amazonas Military Commander </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2801012194 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
26 Jan 94 p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2801012194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Manaus -- PT [Workers Party] President and virtual 
presidential candidate Luis Inacio Lula da Silva yesterday 
announced that he will meet with the three military ministers by 
April at the latest. He made this announcement during a visit 
to General Jose Sampaio Maia, the Amazonas military commander. 
According to Lula's advisers, the PT candidate's first formal 
meeting with a military commander lasted 105 minutes, and 
addressed "problems of the Amazonas." 
  Lula said he intends to expedite the meetings with the 
military sector in order to become better acquainted with the 
situation of the military, and to complete the program of 
government proposed by the PT. After his meeting with the 
Amazonas military commander, Lula was enthusiastic about the 
receptivity he found within the military. In exchange for this, 
he advocated a stronger military presence in the Amazonas: "It 
is necessary to give the Armed Forces a good structure to 
maintain the security of our borders and continue with their 
positive policy of presence in the area," he said. 

</TEXT>

