<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 27 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2701153194 </F>
<F P=103> PY2701153194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Peru monitored through 27 
January. Source is listed in parentheses following each item: 
  The Inter-American Development Bank, IDB, has approved new 
loans for Peru totaling $300 million, which will be earmarked 
for health and education projects as well as for a program to 
grant property deeds to poor peasants. This information was 
made public on 9 January by Manuel Estela, the Peruvian 
representative to the IDB. He reported that this is the first 
part of $400 million in loans the IDB intends to grant to Peru 
1994. The Financial Development Corporation will be in charge 
of administering the funds. (Lima LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 10 
Jan 94 p 7) 
  The Netherlands' Government has officially notified Economy 
Minister Jorge Camet Dickmann of the partial forgiveness of 
Peru's debt to the Netherlands for the granting of loans on 
concessionary terms, which amounts to $1.9 billion. The 
Netherlands canceled a total of $6.7 billion of Peruvian debt in 
1993. (Lima EL COMERCIO in Spanish 14 Jan 94 p A4) 

</TEXT>

