<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Office Warns Against Parallel Institution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2801231894 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2801231894 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Senate office warns against the formation of a 
parallel office at the initiative of certain senators and of 
those whose election on 18 January is contested. The office, led 
by Senator Firmin Jean-Louis, indicates that the various 
resolutions issued by this parallel office cannot in any way 
contribute to the solution to the crisis. The office advises the 
concerned parties that any act emerging from those sessions, 
which are considered illegal, can compromise the parliamentary 
institution. 
  The Senate office invites the 18 January elected to regain 
their self-control, to respect their identities, and to let the 
senators' assembly work on the burning issues of the moment. 

</TEXT>

