<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner on Government Points for Talks With EZLN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2901193994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1902 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2901193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, Mexico 29 Jan (EFE) -- 
Manuel Camacho Solis, peace and reconciliation commissioner, 
today (Saturday) reported seven points [puntos] of the Mexican 
Government to begin peace talks with the rebel Zapatista 
National Liberation Army (EZLN). 
  During a news conference in San Cristobal de las Casas, 
approximately 750 km southeast of the Mexican capital, Camacho 
Solis said conditions do exist for peace, but he concluded he 
does not know whether prompt negotiations will begin with the 
rebels. 

</TEXT>

