<H3> <TI>   Di Tella Says U.S. To Invite Argentina To Join NAFTA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2801173994 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2801173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Argentine Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella has said 
in Washington that the United States will invite Argentina to 
join the North American Free Trade Agreement, NAFTA. He added 
that the United States will make this official before July 1994 
and that the decision will not affect Mercosur [Common Market of 
the South]. 
  Di Tella said this is a very important step toward the 
original idea of achieving a free trade zone in the Americas. 

