<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Meet UN's Ghali; Aware of Chilean Trip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2801172894 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1335 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2801172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Buenos Aires, 28 Jan (NA) -- Foreign Minister 
Guido Di Tella today stated that security and drug trafficking 
are on the agenda he will discuss with UN Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali on 31 January in New York. 
  Di Tella has been in Washington since 26 January discussing 
several topics with State Department officials. The definition 
of the purchase of the A-4M planes equipped with the most 
up-to-date radars and the retooling of the Falda del Carmen 
plant are among the topics he is discussing. 
  The Argentine foreign minister stated that he is aware of 
the 
trip by Chilean congressmen to the Malvinas Islands "for purely 
ecological reasons," adding that "they promised to pass on their 
impressions upon their return." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

