<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Envoy: Working Paper `Mere Understanding' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3112202893 Cairo MENA in English 1622 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC3112202893 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, Dec 31 (MENA)--The Palestinian-Israeli 
working paper which was reached by both sides was just a mere 
understanding and not an agreement, Palestinian Ambassador to 
Egypt Sa'id Kamal said today. 
  Thus, the paper called for presenting the text to both the 
Palestinian and Israeli leaderships, Ambassador Kamal told MENA. 
  Palestinian leader Yasir 'Arafat agreed that Taba 
committee's 
meetings would resume during next week, Ambassador Kamal further 
said. 
  Such a meeting was essential to formulate many issues 
regarding Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and Jericho and which 
were agreed on during the past two months, he added. 
  The Palestinians and Israelis could continue contacts to 
clear barriers which were still impeding the implementation of 
Gaza-Jericho peace accord, he said. 
  He reiterated the importance of the efforts exerted by 
President Husni Mubarak to surmount the difficulties impeding 
the execution of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of 
Principles. 
  The coming summit of 'Arafat and Israeli Premier Yitzhaq 
Rabin would take place by mid January at most in the light of 
the progress made by the negotiations, he said. 

</TEXT>

