<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contacts Under Way To Clear `Misunderstanding' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0201095394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0915 GMT 2 Jan 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC0201095394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jan (MENA)--The Palestinians and Israelis 
are making intensive contacts with each other, both directly and 
via intermediaries, notably Egypt, to eliminate the 
misunderstanding between their leaders which have delayed the 
implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement. 
  Muhammad Subayh, secretary of the Palestine National 
Council, 
told MENA that the misunderstanding resulted from the fact that 
the contents of several documents that had been submitted were 
inaccurately conveyed to the leaders. 
  Subayh explained that the points raised by President Yasir 
'Arafat in connection with the Gaza-Jericho agreement are part 
and parcel of the Palestinian-Israeli Declaration of Principles 
signed in Washington 13 September. 
  Subayh stressed that the Palestinians have a definite wish 
to 
implement the Gaza-Jericho agreement and they believe that the 
Israelis have the same wish. 

</TEXT>

