<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa To Arrive in Israel To Help Bridge Gaps </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0301121294 Jerusalem AL-MANAR in Arabic 3 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> TA0301121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem AL-MANAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Egyptian Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa is expected to 
arrive in Israel to discuss the points of contention between the 
Palestinian and Israeli sides that emerged during the recent 
Cairo talks. Cairo is trying to bridge the gap between the two 
sides and achieve agreement on implementing the declaration of 
principles. It is worth noting that Egypt is playing a key role 
in support of the peace process. 

</TEXT>

