<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat `Optimistic' on Differences With Israel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0101194794 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 1 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0101194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat], president of 
the state of Palestine and PLO Executive Committee chairman, has 
said that he remains optimistic the differences with Israel 
concerning the implementation of the Declaration of Principles 
can be worked out. His remark came in an interview with the 
Britith Sky Television network screened last night. The 
disagreements between the PLO and Israel should not stand in the 
way of implementing the Gaza-Jericho accord, 'Arafat stated. It 
is an international document the signing of which was witnessed 
by the cosponsors of the Middle East peace process, President 
Bill Clinton, and the whole world, he noted. 

</TEXT>

