<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Team To Visit Amman, Sign Economic Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0301084594 Amman AL-WATAN in Arabic 2 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN0301084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-WATAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Amman--AL-WATAN has learned from informed 
Palestinian sources that a high-level Palestinian delegation 
will arrive in Amman this week, and that the delegation will 
sign Jordanian-PLO economic agreements that have been finalized 
by special bilateral committees. 
  This official visit will come on the heels of recent talks 
held between His Majesty King Husayn and the Palestinian 
president, during which the Palestinian side affirmed its 
concern to maintain the special Palestinian-Jordanian 
relationship regardless of the impediments entailed. 
  In a separate development, Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali received at his office yesterday Dr. George Habash, 
secretary general of the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine, who arrived in Amman the day before yesterday. 
  AL-WATAN has learned that there is currently a consensus 
within the Palestinian side, particularly the PLO leadership, 
that the Israeli leaders will maintain their procrastination and 
prevarication regarding the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho 
accord, and that it is in the interest of the Palestinians to 
coordinate with various Palestinian factions and forces to 
ensure harmony within the Palestinian camp, and also to enhance 
the relationship with Jordan and other Arab sides. 

</TEXT>

