<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fundamentalist' Killed; Police Attacked </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3012124893 Paris AFP in English 1051 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> NC3012124893 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Algiers, Dec 30 (AFP)--An Islamic fundamentalist was 
killed by security forces when three armed men raided a post 
office in Fouka 25 kilometres (15 miles) from the Algerian 
capital, the newspaper LIBERTE reported on Thursday. 
  The other two men got away in a waiting car. 
  At Iferhounene, half a dozen armed men attacked the police 
station and administrative offices but there were no casualties, 
EL MOUDJAHID reported. 
  At Azazga, in the same region of the Great Kabyle massif, an 
armed gang on Wednesday got away with 600,000 dinars (26,000 
dollars) from a branch of the Local Development Bank. 

</TEXT>

