<H3> <TI>   Newspaper Criticizes Rabin's Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0201075194 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0615 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0201075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Jan (MENA)--Newspaper AL-JUMHURIYAH notes 
that Israeli Prime Minister Rabin's remarks regarding the draft 
compromise document, which was submitted during the 
Israeli-Palestinian talks in Cairo, and the need to accept this 
draft represents a new setback for the peace efforts. The paper 
says that the remarks are also bound to torpedo the principle of 
dialogue and negotiations that has been pursued by the parties 
to the conflict as a way to resolve an issue that has been going 
on for years. 
  In its editorial today, AL-JUMHURIYAH states the belief that 
these remarks demonstrate that the Israeli tactics in 
negotiating and in dealing with the issues at hand will 
negatively affect the other tracks. 
  The paper goes on to say that the fact that Rabin's 
statements were made following the laying of the cornerstones of 
20 new West Bank settlements raises questions about Israel's 
intentions and Rabin's credibility. 
  AL-JUMHURIYAH maintains that the policy of playing for time 
cannot wipe out the rights of the wronged nations that are 
struggling to wrest back their legitimate rights. The paper 
concludes its editorial by saying that this policy is a time 
bomb that will open wide the door of violence. 

</TEXT>

