<H3> <TI>   Fahd Replies to Clinton Cable on Shura Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012144693 Riyadh SPA in English 1224 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD3012144693 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, Dec 30, SPA -- Custodian of the two holy 
mosques, King Fahd Bin-'Abd al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud received last 
night a cable from the U.S. President Bill Clinton over the 
inauguration of the Shoura Council. President Clinton expressed 
pleasure on the occasion and welcomed the developments 
concerning the establishment of the Shura Council and regional 
councils as important steps that cope with the history and 
traditions of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. 
  He congratulated King Fahd, the royal family and the Saudi 
people on the political reforms. 
  Replying the cable, King Fahd thanked President Clinton on 
the friendly contents of the cable and expressed good wishes to 
President Clinton and the American people. King Fahd expressed 
hope that the Saudi Government would continue the welfare march 
of development and construction. 

</TEXT>

