<H3> <TI>   Salih Receives Message From UAE President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3012143793 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 30 Dec 92 </F>

<F P=103> JN3012143793 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of 
the Presidential Council, has received a message from his 
brother His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, 
president of the fraternal United Arab Emirates [UAE]. The 
message deals with brotherly relations between the two 
countries, as well as issues of interest to our Arab nation. 
The message also includes ways of bolstering brotherly 
cooperation with our country, unifying the word of the brothers, 
purifying the Arab atmosphere, and restoring Arab solidarity and 
cooperation. 
  The message was conveyed by UAE Ambassador in Sanaa Sayf 
al-Mansuri, who met the brother president today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

