1400 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0201150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to reports government forces have foiled 
a big attack on Kabul by forces of General Dostam and Mahmud 
Barialay and as a result the situation in the city have now 
relatively eased. A spokesman of the Afghan Embassy in Islamabad 
in a press conference today claimed that the Islamic Army of 
Afghanistan have captured many areas including (Pol-e Mahmud 
Khan), Chaman Hozuri, Khawaja Rawash Airport, Bala Hesar, 
(Chapaibibi Mehroh), and Mazar-e-Sharif Airport. He said the 
enemy forces have suffered heavy losses. About 200 persons have 
been killed during fighting and at least 12 tanks captured. He 
said fierce fighting is still going on in Faryab Province, as 
well as, in the Province of (Shabergam). 

