<H3> <TI>   Garang Rebels Accused of Attacking Refugee Camp </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA3012173493 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1315 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> EA3012173493 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today's AL-INQADH AL-WATANI newspaper carries a 
report from Kampala saying that a group of 51 armed rebels from 
rebel Garang's faction attacked the camp housing Sudanese 
refugees at (Dango) in Zaire, with the aim of liquidating some 
elements. Four citizens in the camp were killed. Firing 
continued for over (?an hour). 
  The report states that the Zairian forces succeeded in 
capturing one of the rebels, after which the group of rebel 
Garang threatened to kill the official in charge of (Dango), the 
police officer, and the official in charge of the refugees, 
unless a detained rebel who had participated in the attack was 
handed over. 
  The Zairian authorities have condemned the aggression 
inflicted by the rebels on refugee camps and refused the rebel 
demand. In response to the rebel provocations, they have sent a 
large force of Zairian soldiers to secure the camp and the 
surrounding area. UNHCR headquarters in Geneva has been 
informed about the incident. 

</TEXT>

