<H3> <TI>   Belgian Release of JKLF Leader Questioned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3012130493 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> BK3012130493 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the Rajya Sabha, the opposition today expressed 
concern over the reported decision of the Belgian Government to 
deport the JKLF [Jammu Kashmir Liberation Front] chief, 
Amanullah Khan, to Pakistan. Raising the issue during zero hour 
[time when there is nothing on the agenda], Mr. J.P. Mathur, BJP 
[Bharatiya Janata Party]; Mr. I.J. Gujral, Janata Dal; and 
others said Amanullah Khan was arrested in Brussels on a warrant 
issued by India. They asked the government to clarify whether 
the Indian case was effectively presented in the Brussels court. 

</TEXT>

