<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Comments on Negotiations, `Understandings' </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Palestinians Should Start Sweating Now' </H4>
<F P=102> TA0201104894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 2 Jan 
93 </F>

<F P=103> TA0201104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rabin and Foreign Minister Peres 
decided to resume the economic talks between Israel and the PLO 
in Paris this week. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that 
a Finance Ministry team will depart for Paris tomorrow. It is 
possible that the heads of the delegations, Finance Minister 
Avraham Shohat and the PLO's Abu-al-'Ala' [Ahmad Quray'], will 
arrive in Paris toward the end of the week. 
  At the opening of today's cabinet meeting Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin spoke with great firmness against the way in which 
the Palestinians are conducting the negotiations. The prime 
minister said he is willing to resume the Taba talks only on the 
basis of the understandings reached in Cairo. Mr. Rabin said 
that Israel is in no hurry, and that the Palestinians should 
start sweating now. According to Rabin, over the last few days 
it has transpired that we cannot count on oral understandings 
with the PLO leaders, and henceforth he will demand that all the 
understandings reached with them be written down. 
  Earlier today Prime Minister Rabin and Foreign Minister 
Peres 
held an hour-long private meeting. The prime minister also held 
consultations with various security services elements, and this 
afternoon these consultations will continue. 

</TEXT>

