<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Comments on Negotiations, `Understandings' </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Understandings' Must Be Starting Point </H4>
<F P=102> TA0201141194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 2 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0201141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israel will today issue an unequivocal announcement 
to the PLO in Tunis that the Taba talks will resume only on the 
understanding that the negotiations' starting point are the 
understandings already reached in Cairo. Israel insists that 
neither of the parties raise any demands that contravene these 
understandings. 
  Speaking at the end of today's cabinet session, the prime 
minister said that the draft formulated in Cairo was not an 
Israeli position paper, but rather understandings reached at the 
most senior level between Israel and the PLO. It is 
inconceivable, Yitzhaq Rabin said, not to honor understandings 
reached at such a level and to then start haggling about them. 
This kind of situation, Rabin said, raised doubts about whether 
there was any point at all in reaching such understandings. If 
the Palestinians reject the understandings, Rabin said, 
everything is open. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

