<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Others React to Israel-Vatican Ties </TI></H3>
<H4>   Fadlallah Criticizes Move </H4>
<F P=102> NC0101111894 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1000 
GMT 1 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0101111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] 'Allamah Muhammad Husayn Fadlallah has stressed that 
the Vatican's recognition of Israel is not a Christian 
recognition. He noted that the new year marks the death of an 
old era and the birth of a new one. He added: We told the 
Vatican, which we respect, that if Christ were here now he would 
expel the Jews from the temple as he did the thieves, because 
the Jews are the thieves of security, politics, and economy. 
Therefore, the Vatican's recognition of Israel is not Christian 
because we believe in Christ's values, which are ones of right 
and justice. To recognize Israel, he added, is to recognize its 
injustice against the Arabs and the Palestinians. 
  'Allamah Fadlallah noted that the United States stands 
against any righteous and just position in the Third World and 
is working with its full power against the Islamists and to 
besiege the Islamic Republic of Iran. He added: While we 
believe that the United States is the enemy of the peoples and 
justice, we have no problem with the American people but rather 
our problem is with the U.S. Administration. Our problem with 
this administration is that there is no U.S. policy in the 
region, there is an Israeli policy. 

</TEXT>

