<H3> <TI>   Officials, Others React to Israel-Vatican Ties </TI></H3>
<H4>   Junblatt Condemns `Hostile Alliance' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0301074694 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 0530 
GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0301074694 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Progressive Socialist Party Leader Minister Walid 
Junblatt has condemned the Vatican's recognition of Israel and 
described it as an alliance hostile to Arabism and Islam. This 
action confirms Western-Jewish plotting against the region and 
its peoples, resources, and identity. He said that the 
Vatican's recognition of Israel 500 years after the fall of 
Granada is a Zionist Jewish victory in the world, particularly 
in the mother Christian church in Rome. 
  Junblatt added: Perhaps we cannot assess now all 
implications of this Western-Zionist alliance, but we can say 
that our Arab identity and our Islamic identity are in danger. 
Pope John Paul's upcoming visits to Lebanon and occupied 
Palestine come within this context and cap this alliance. Any 
other talk about the pope's visit is meaningless. He said: The 
church leaders in Lebanon--who now advocate human rights, 
freedom, and other resounding slogans--were mute when Beirut was 
pounded during the Israeli invasion and when the Lebanese 
Government signed the 17 May accord with the Israeli Government. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

