<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad Talks With Arab Leaders, Christopher </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN3112214593 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 2115 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> JN3112214593 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad today received a phone call 
from Lebanese President Ilyas al-Hirawi. The two presidents 
exchanged congratulations on the new year. They also discussed 
latest developments in the region. 
  President Hafiz al-Asad this evening received a phone call 
from His Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal. The president and his 
majesty the king exchanged congratulations on the new year. 
They also talked about issues of interest to the two fraternal 
countries. 
  The president this evening received a phone call from 
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri, who congratulated the 
president on the new year. Talks also centered on issues of 
interest to Syria and Lebanon. 
  President Hafiz al-Asad this evening received a phone call 
from U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher, who 
congratulated the president on the new year. He also conveyed 
U.S. President Bill Clinton's greetings and congratulations on 
the new year. The president thanked him, exchanged 
congratulations with him, and asked him to convey his greetings 
and congratulations to President Clinton on the new year. 
During the contact, they also discussed the meeting which will 
be held between the president and President Clinton in Geneva as 
well as the upcoming visit to the region by a U.S. congressional 
delegation to discuss missing Israeli soldiers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

